<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="20 years Coast Guard hazmat, now chasing a CCNA and building a home lab."
	pubDate={new Date('July 16 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		I'm Kit — Christian Applegate if you're being formal about it. I spent 20 years in the
		Coast Guard as a Marine Science Technician, which is a fancy way of saying I dealt with
		hazmat for a living. I worked as a foreign vessel inspector, a facility inspector, and a
		federal on-scene coordinator representative, which meant showing up when something had
		already gone wrong and helping sort out the mess.
	</p>
	<p>
		Four of those twenty years I spent as an instructor at Training Center Yorktown, teaching
		the MST A-school. That might be the part of my career I'm proudest of — watching people
		walk in knowing nothing and walk out with enough to actually start their career. Turns out
		I like teaching almost as much as I like the work itself.
	</p>
	<p>
		Now I'm retired from that life and starting a new one in IT — network engineering,
		specifically, working toward my CCNA, with a serious side interest in AI. I want to
		understand the whole stack, not just use the tools. It's a huge switch, career-wise, and
		if I'm honest it's exactly the kind of questionable decision this blog is named after.
		<strong>Kit Bashing</strong> is where I'm cataloging that whole mess: the certs, the home
		lab I'm building from scratch, the AI projects I can't stop starting, and whatever breaks
		along the way.
	</p>
</Layout>
